You should've seen the note.

18:15.512 --> 18:18.765
So, why didn't she tell you
where she was going, if she was going?

18:18.765 --> 18:22.477
Look, she had issues with the family,
all right? I don't need to get into that.

18:22.477 --> 18:24.771
Let's just say there was all of us
and then there was her.

18:24.771 --> 18:26.481
We busted our humps to make a living.

18:26.481 --> 18:28.817
And she spent it all going to art school, okay?

18:28.817 --> 18:31.153
We were businesspeople, she wasn't.

18:31.153 --> 18:33.739
Oh, yeah. Oh, yeah.

18:33.739 --> 18:35.073
Fuck me, sailor.

18:35.782 --> 18:37.868
- So, when's that book coming out?
- About a year.

18:37.868 --> 18:39.536
I've got other families I gotta talk to.

18:39.536 --> 18:41.205
- I'll be in touch.
- Hold on.

18:41.747 --> 18:45.209
- Come with me for a sec.
- Oh, no. Fuck, fuck, fuck.

18:45.209 --> 18:47.252
- So there is a reward, right?
- Yeah.

18:47.252 --> 18:50.380
Gonna offer you a free tanning session
because I can't look at you.

18:51.173 --> 18:53.800
Yes, Tony! Yeah! Yes!

18:56.512 --> 18:57.721
Is that a lithograph?

19:02.559 --> 19:04.311
This is oil on canvas.

19:04.311 --> 19:05.771
Yeah. Dona did that.

19:08.398 --> 19:09.483
Dona did this?

19:11.360 --> 19:12.569
It looks like a Magritte.

19:14.780 --> 19:18.367
That's Magritte's wife, actually.
You know the history of this thing?

19:18.367 --> 19:21.787
History is he had a wife that's
a little too chunky, at least for me.

19:21.787 --> 19:24.790
I mean, I go for a broad,
flat stomach, nice tan.

19:24.790 --> 19:27.042
But Dona, she loved this shit.

19:28.001 --> 19:30.379
Anyway, come on. Jump in.
Come on. Let's go, come on.

19:32.464 --> 19:34.091
What did you do?

19:34.091 --> 19:36.718
Oh, yeah. Lionel Richie is
a sad little fuck these days.

19:37.344 --> 19:40.305
She had him 30 years.
And he was like her kid.

19:41.056 --> 19:43.058
Plucked all his fucking feathers out
when she left.

19:43.058 --> 19:45.686
Fuck me, Daddy. Oh, no.

19:47.396 --> 19:48.397
Oh, yeah.

19:50.357 --> 19:53.277
Evidently, she had a thing
for Lionel Richie, but whatever.

19:53.986 --> 19:57.072
The point is, she made replicas
of stolen masterpieces,

19:57.072 --> 19:59.908
<i>and the swami sold them to mobsters.</i>

19:59.908 --> 20:03.036
<i>I mean</i>,
<i>all signs point to Donatella's dead.</i>

20:03.912 --> 20:07.833
- Poor Dona.
- I know. It's a loss to humanity, Carol.

20:08.667 --> 20:09.918
The girl could paint.

20:09.918 --> 20:14.464
I mean, I'm not an art appraiser per se
but I got an eye.

20:14.464 --> 20:15.924
<i>And for a second there,</i>

20:15.924 --> 20:18.886
<i>I thought I was looking
at an honest-to-God Magritte.</i>

20:19.970 --> 20:22.347
Plus, that bird knows
more than it's saying.

20:23.807 --> 20:26.852
Why do you think he killed her?
Was he jealous?

20:26.852 --> 20:30.314
Yeah. They were running the scam,
and something went wrong.

20:30.314 --> 20:33.150
That guru's got blood
and bird shit on his hands.

20:33.150 --> 20:35.319
I gotta go pick up
that missing persons report.

20:35.861 --> 20:38.113
Hey! Get the hell out of my car!

20:38.113 --> 20:40.324
I gotta go defuse a lunatic.
Meet me at Mommy's.

20:40.324 --> 20:43.368
Are you nuts?
Who gets into someone else's car?

20:43.368 --> 20:44.786
Yeah, my bad. I'm late.

20:44.786 --> 20:46.288
You were blocking me.

20:46.288 --> 20:48.498
Honey, I've shot people for less.

20:48.498 --> 20:50.375
Well, then it's my lucky day, right?

20:51.460 --> 20:52.461
Are those acrylics?

20:55.339 --> 20:57.925
Yeah. I did them.

20:58.675 --> 20:59.593
That's my shop.

20:59.593 --> 21:00.719
Wowza.

21:02.346 --> 21:03.514
May I?

21:05.474 --> 21:07.643
Wow. How do you do that?

21:07.643 --> 21:08.977
Experience.

21:08.977 --> 21:11.855
Well, it's not just that, it's a gift.

21:13.148 --> 21:15.108
Stop by. I'll give you a discount.

21:15.901 --> 21:17.152
Okay.

21:17.152 --> 21:18.237
Don't do that again.

21:18.237 --> 21:19.446
Thank you.

21:21.365 --> 21:24.618
Missing persons report.
Dona Scarborough left a note for Bob.

21:29.206 --> 21:31.124
- Wow. So mean.
- Right?

21:31.124 --> 21:33.168
So she did leave. She left.

21:33.168 --> 21:34.461
But she left Lionel Richie.

21:34.461 --> 21:38.382
She loved that fucking bird.
Even though it has a very foul mouth.

21:38.882 --> 21:43.262
Now it lives in a whorehouse
plucking out its feathers. Brokenhearted.

21:44.638 --> 21:46.640
He killed her. I'm sure of it.

21:48.433 --> 21:49.935
I should go get that bird.

21:50.644 --> 21:51.770
You're so sweet.

21:51.770 --> 21:54.106
You would take in a bald bird?

21:54.606 --> 21:55.732
Such a caring person.

21:55.732 --> 21:58.902
I don't know if I'll be able to sleep
tonight thinking about that bird.

21:59.403 --> 22:01.572
This world is just too much.

22:02.281 --> 22:03.115
Hey.

22:04.700 --> 22:09.788
We just have to carry that, Carol.
We just have to carry it.

22:10.914 --> 22:14.668
PS, you should reach out to your sister
because Stewart pressures her.

22:14.668 --> 22:17.462
You know how he is. He's trapped in stone.

22:17.462 --> 22:19.548
You said
he didn't even cry at the funeral.

22:19.548 --> 22:20.966
Not a tear.

22:20.966 --> 22:22.968
Not even when I sang
"The Wind Beneath My Wings."

22:22.968 --> 22:24.344
What?

22:24.928 --> 22:27.097
I should've released doves too.

22:27.097 --> 22:29.933
Regret. It feels like acid reflux.

22:31.894 --> 22:33.687
Anyway, I tried to reach out to her.

22:35.355 --> 22:37.232
So, try again?

22:47.701 --> 22:49.453
Dianne. Hey.

22:49.453 --> 22:52.789
Do me a favor, meet me at P. Town.
I have something to show you.

22:54.208 --> 22:55.209
What do you mean "no?"

22:56.126 --> 22:58.712
Okay, fine,
then I'll just tell you on the phone.

22:58.712 --> 23:00.881
Look, I found some naughty shit
you wrote in high school

23:00.881 --> 23:03.008
that you tried to submit
to <i>Penthouse Forum</i>.

23:03.592 --> 23:06.845
Some fantasy about
being in a dugout with Lenny Dykstra.

23:07.471 --> 23:10.432
Mommy held onto it.
She was always so proud of you.

23:11.433 --> 23:14.102
Anyhow, I could send it
to your house but if your kid--

23:15.896 --> 23:18.524
Okay. Well, I'll see you then.

23:20.275 --> 23:21.276
Yay.

23:22.444 --> 23:25.447
<i>Come back to the bunkhouse
just out of Pioneertown.</i>

23:40.170 --> 23:41.797
For your mother. And you.

23:42.589 --> 23:46.134
Peggy, did you know Ginger
was a regular in <i>Knight Rider</i>?

23:46.134 --> 23:48.053
Semi-regular. Semi.

23:48.053 --> 23:52.266
Excuse me. Does the talent go in
and make paper dolls out of the ledgers?

23:52.266 --> 23:55.394
And if she's on a horse,
who's got their eyes on the books?

23:56.144 --> 23:58.021
Anything could be happening right now.

23:59.731 --> 24:00.858
Excuse me. No!

24:00.858 --> 24:05.153
Now they're eating each other's faces.
That's not accurate to the period.

24:05.153 --> 24:07.030
Don't stress over a man.

24:07.030 --> 24:11.076
I say be like a cat. Let them come to you.

24:11.869 --> 24:13.453
How long you been single?

24:14.413 --> 24:16.081
Thirty-four years.

24:18.542 --> 24:20.878
Hey, how'd you like
to make some real money?

24:21.628 --> 24:23.338
I'm not making any kind of money.

24:23.338 --> 24:25.716
How'd you like to play an art buyer?

24:27.759 --> 24:31.972
I played an art enthusiast
in <i>The Thomas Crown Affair</i>.

24:32.806 --> 24:33.891
"It's nice."

24:35.601 --> 24:36.810
That was my line.

24:37.603 --> 24:40.314
Russo was threatened.
She made them cut it.

24:41.398 --> 24:44.610
Okay. Ginger, go inside. Get in character.

24:45.194 --> 24:46.737
- Hi!
- <i>All right. I'm here.</i>

24:46.737 --> 24:47.946
Hey!

24:47.946 --> 24:48.947
Hi.

24:49.531 --> 24:51.450
- Okay, you ready?
- Ready for what?

24:51.450 --> 24:54.828
Okay. Just do a scene with fake Mommy.

24:54.828 --> 24:56.455
Just say everything you couldn't say.

24:56.455 --> 24:58.123
It'll help. I swear on my life.

24:59.374 --> 25:00.918
What about the <i>Penthouse</i> letter?

25:00.918 --> 25:03.962
I threw that filthy thing away
'cause I look out for you.

25:04.630 --> 25:07.049
Remember when I read
that fucking coach the riot act

25:07.049 --> 25:08.842
for not letting you play Little League?

25:09.551 --> 25:11.470
I always believed in you. Okay?

25:13.931 --> 25:15.432
Just give me ten minutes.

25:18.852 --> 25:20.145
Ginger!

25:20.145 --> 25:22.189
Since we're
workshopping this indefinitely,

25:22.189 --> 25:25.651
Dianne here will be playing
another daughter for a while.

25:25.651 --> 25:28.111
- Dianne...
- Can you not use my real name, please?

25:28.111 --> 25:30.656
...Isis. Dianisis. Okay.

25:30.656 --> 25:36.912
You're on your deathbed obviously,
and you and Dianisis have lost contact.

25:37.663 --> 25:41.333
No one could really get over
what happened when Jerry left.

25:41.917 --> 25:42.918
Bastard.

25:43.794 --> 25:47.214
You recall the scene
when Stewart is sucking his thumb.

25:47.881 --> 25:50.133
- How old's this kid again?
- He's nine.

25:50.801 --> 25:53.762
Is there something wrong with him?
It's a little old to suck your thumb.

25:54.721 --> 25:57.182
This is a "no shame zone," Ginger.

25:58.267 --> 25:59.768
I can't do this.

25:59.768 --> 26:02.354
I'm sorry. It's just too weird.

26:02.354 --> 26:04.022
Hey. No, get back down.

26:04.022 --> 26:06.817
You're on your deathbed
in and out of worlds.

26:07.526 --> 26:08.610
Dianisis.

26:09.361 --> 26:11.405
You have to tell Mommy
how you really feel.

26:11.405 --> 26:15.367
Look at her.
She's open, completely available to hear.

26:16.159 --> 26:19.079
Just open your heart, open your mouth.

26:19.830 --> 26:22.541
She's ready to hear.

26:23.750 --> 26:26.044
- Hold the work in the saloon!
- Sorry, Peg.

26:26.044 --> 26:27.129
Come on.

26:28.005 --> 26:29.214
Stay with the moment.

26:31.800 --> 26:35.637
Stay in this moment. And... action!

26:42.352 --> 26:46.648
Mommy, I didn't see you before you died.

26:46.648 --> 26:48.066
Were you scared?

26:50.068 --> 26:52.279
Course I was. Who wouldn't be?

26:53.071 --> 26:54.781
Ginger, you're unconscious.

26:58.368 --> 27:00.329
Okay, I remember before Daddy left,

27:00.329 --> 27:03.957
you took me to see Alvin Ailey
in the city and we sat way up top,

27:04.708 --> 27:10.380
and you cried...
because you were just so in awe.

27:11.173 --> 27:13.926
And then we went for ice cream
at Grand Central Station,

27:13.926 --> 27:17.304
and you told me
you wanted to be a dancer once.

27:20.641 --> 27:22.559
And then I fell asleep on the train.

27:24.061 --> 27:27.105
And that day, you were all mine.

27:30.234 --> 27:33.028
But then Daddy left,
and you turned into a ghost.

27:36.240 --> 27:38.617
People die before they die sometimes.

27:41.036 --> 27:43.539
I kept trying to get you to see me again...

27:45.999 --> 27:46.959
but it hurt too much.

27:46.959 --> 27:48.418
I couldn't do it anymore!

27:50.087 --> 27:52.339
I see people waiting for me.

27:54.174 --> 27:58.011
I just thought that if I was good enough,
that if I was successful enough,

27:58.011 --> 27:59.179
you would come back.

28:01.181 --> 28:02.182
But you were gone.

28:07.104 --> 28:09.273
Mommy, I just wanna say that I love you.

28:11.567 --> 28:13.068
Okay? And--

28:15.571 --> 28:16.989
And I forgive you.

28:26.039 --> 28:27.666
I forgive you too.

28:28.876 --> 28:31.128
You're unconscious, Ginger!

28:31.128 --> 28:33.255
What? For what?
What would you forgive me for?

28:33.255 --> 28:35.090
For being selfish.

28:35.841 --> 28:36.925
What is she doing?

28:36.925 --> 28:39.386
It just felt right.
She's a little clingy.

28:39.386 --> 28:41.513
Oh, my-- This is bullshit.

28:42.306 --> 28:44.016
Screw this. She sucks.

28:47.728 --> 28:49.688
It was kind of cathartic though, right?

28:49.688 --> 28:53.233
Cathartic? Peggy, no!
I actually feel worse now.

28:53.734 --> 28:55.277
She was not a good Mommy.

28:55.277 --> 28:57.696
I know. That makes two of them.

29:06.830 --> 29:09.791
Oh, my-- Would you just go away? Please!

29:12.002 --> 29:13.837
You really shit the bed on that one.

29:14.755 --> 29:16.507
I hope you're a better art buyer.

29:30.437 --> 29:31.605
It's nice.

29:31.605 --> 29:34.399
Nice? Yeah, it's a Cézanne.

29:34.900 --> 29:36.026
Don't get touchy.

29:36.026 --> 29:38.695
- It's a fucking Cézanne.
- It's quite classic,

29:38.695 --> 29:41.448
from a modern sort of modality.

29:41.448 --> 29:44.243
Or the other way around,
I think, actually.

29:47.037 --> 29:48.539
900,000?

29:48.539 --> 29:50.123
Not even close.

29:50.123 --> 29:53.836
- Why don't you go call your guy?
- Oh, yes. Yes! Yes.

29:53.836 --> 29:57.881
Now is the time. Indeed.

29:59.550 --> 30:00.634
Is she mentally ill?

30:00.634 --> 30:02.553
She's on the spectrum.

30:02.553 --> 30:04.721
But she's totally legit.

30:04.721 --> 30:06.431
The point is, her guy is loaded.

30:06.431 --> 30:08.976
We need someone for Kachel to bid against.

30:08.976 --> 30:10.477
He's gotta feel the heat.

30:10.477 --> 30:12.688
Wait. She's not working for our guy?

30:12.688 --> 30:14.439
I thought
she was working for James Kachel.

30:14.439 --> 30:17.526
No, she works for a guy
that Kachel fucking hates.

30:17.526 --> 30:19.945
You told me
she was working for James Kachel.

30:20.737 --> 30:26.326
Do you want 1.3? Did you tell me
you wanted 1.3, or didn't ya?

30:26.326 --> 30:28.996
- Yeah.
- Well, this is how we get to 1.3.

30:32.165 --> 30:36.545
Yes, I certainly will, sir. Yes. Ciao.

30:39.590 --> 30:43.427
- We'll be in touch.
- Okay. Don't touch. Come, come.

30:45.012 --> 30:46.096
<i>How bad is it?</i>

30:46.763 --> 30:51.059
It's bad.
I thought it was bad, but it's worse.

30:51.560 --> 30:53.478
Do you have an umbrella? I'm very fair.

30:53.478 --> 30:55.147
How much worse? What do you mean?

30:55.147 --> 30:56.607
Or a hat, maybe?

30:56.607 --> 30:59.109
<i>I mean,
I might have to declare bankruptcy.</i>

30:59.943 --> 31:02.738
You can't declare bankruptcy.

31:02.738 --> 31:05.908
I'm inches away from a payday.
This is my life's work.

31:06.867 --> 31:08.035
What am I gonna do?

31:09.661 --> 31:11.705
I can't do anything else. I'm an asshole.

31:11.705 --> 31:14.458
Look, just give me today, maybe tomorrow.

31:14.958 --> 31:16.960
Okay. By Thursday.

31:16.960 --> 31:19.421
<i>Just keep it together. Semper fi.</i>

31:20.088 --> 31:21.215
Semper fi.

31:24.885 --> 31:27.513
<i>In today's qigong instruction,</i>

31:27.513 --> 31:30.641
<i>we will be concentrating on
sealing our gates.</i>

31:32.017 --> 31:33.644
<i>Squeeze the buttocks.</i>

31:35.062 --> 31:36.563
<i>And tilt the pelvis.</i>

31:41.276 --> 31:42.361
Who is that?

31:43.487 --> 31:44.655
This is Judy.

31:45.155 --> 31:47.699
- Judy, huh?
- Some SOB left her in a hot car.

31:47.699 --> 31:51.828
I was like, "Nope, that's not gonna
happen today. You're coming with me."

31:51.828 --> 31:52.913
Right, Judy?

31:53.455 --> 31:56.166
All right. I'm gonna help you
get the silver back for 60%

31:56.166 --> 31:58.544
since you should've given it to me
in the first place.

31:58.544 --> 32:00.254
- I actually think 50-50 is--
- All right,

32:00.254 --> 32:03.465
do not try to chisel me down
one-eighth of a percent, or I'm out.

32:04.299 --> 32:05.509
Okay.

32:06.176 --> 32:07.344
And I need a favor.

32:07.344 --> 32:08.554
Whatever you need.

32:09.429 --> 32:12.057
You up for a little Miami Shock and Awe?

32:13.684 --> 32:14.726
Who's the mark?

32:16.061 --> 32:17.896
This guru bastard.

32:17.896 --> 32:19.398
What do you wanna know about him?

32:19.398 --> 32:21.358
If he killed his wife.

32:21.358 --> 32:26.363
I'll tell you more if it's necessary
but for now, it's a need-to-know basis.

32:29.616 --> 32:30.868
Okay. Sounds good.

32:32.911 --> 32:34.246
And get the dog off the bed.

32:38.041 --> 32:39.209
How come?

32:39.209 --> 32:40.752
Because we're gonna have sex.

32:40.752 --> 32:42.045
Judy, off the bed.
